00:05:16,501 --> 00:05:24,470
And it is the role of the school committee to make the policy and to review the policies for the school district.

56
00:05:25,811 --> 00:05:29,215
And that's really how you govern, you govern by making policies.

57
00:05:30,757 --> 00:05:48,730
The school committee has an important finance role where they review and approve a budget for education in the district according to a process and timeline developed with the superintendent and the mayor and what other governs our particular city.

58
00:05:50,271 --> 00:05:52,953
The school committee appoints the superintendent.

59
00:05:54,829 --> 00:06:07,158
The school committee also appoints the assistant or associate superintendents, the school business administrator, the administrator of special education, school physicians, and registered nurses.

60
00:06:08,996 --> 00:06:17,804
And we also appoint our own legal counsel and supervisors of attendance.

61
00:06:17,824 --> 00:06:27,734
And they are the superintendent makes a recommendation and the school committee then appoints those particular positions.

62
00:06:29,954 --> 00:06:39,059
The school committee also sets compensation levels for the superintendent and overall compensation limits for other positions.

63
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:43,838
The school committee has a very important role in collective bargaining.

64
00:06:44,638 --> 00:06:53,605
They act as the employer of school employees for school collective bargaining purposes, and they designate a negotiator or a negotiating team.

65
00:06:54,486 --> 00:07:09,157
There are times when the school committee becomes part of that negotiation team, but that's usually, you know, hopefully you might have settled your contract before that becomes a more active role.

66
00:07:11,371 --> 00:07:18,216
And we receive advice from the superintendent about the educational consequences of different bargaining positions.

67
00:07:19,436 --> 00:07:27,942
The school committee establishes upon recommendation of the superintendent, the performance standards for teachers and other employees of the school district.

68
00:07:28,923 --> 00:07:39,791
The school committee evaluates the performance of the superintendent, and that's outlined very carefully in mass general laws on how that is to be done.

69
00:07:42,496 --> 00:07:52,381
It also does a self-evaluation to evaluate the effectiveness of the school committee itself.

70
00:07:53,302 --> 00:08:02,887
The school committee has a role in professional development and adopts a professional development plan for all principal, teachers, and other professional staff.

71
00:08:07,013 --> 00:08:14,481
The school committee receives and approves annual school improvement plans for each school in the district.

72
00:08:17,584 --> 00:08:19,826
The school committee has a role in advocacy.

73
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:27,935
We engage in advocacy on behalf of students and their schools and promote the benefits of a public school system to the community.

74
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:39,046
A school committee has a role in curriculum, approve major adoptions or revisions of curriculum and textbooks upon the recommendation of the superintendent.

75
00:08:40,947 --> 00:08:51,353
The school committee establishes educational goals and policies for the schools in the district consistent with the requirements of law and the statewide goals and standards established by the Board of Education.

76
00:08:53,517 --> 00:09:00,599
The school committee supports the development and promotion of the vision, mission, goals, and strategies of the school committee.

77
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:15,103
School committee members consult and confer with the superintendent on all matters as they arise that concern the school system and on which the school committee may take actions.

78
00:09:19,449 --> 00:09:24,553
And the school committee supports the superintendent in all matters that conform to committee policy.

79
00:09:25,594 --> 00:09:32,399
So I think that those are really gives you a summary of the scope of school committee responsibilities.

